# Key Concepts Covered

## Data Exfiltration

Unauthorized movement of data from an internal environment to an external destination.

Examples include:

- Cloud storage uploads
- Unauthorized file transfers
- Insider threats
- Malware-driven data theft
- Intellectual property theft

---

## Detection Engineering

The investigation demonstrates how threshold-based detections can reduce noise and highlight potentially meaningful activity.

Focus areas include:

- Transfer size analysis
- Alert validation
- Detection tuning
- Signal versus noise reduction

---

## Proxy Log Analysis

Proxy logs were used to identify:

- Upload destinations
- Cloud storage services
- User agents
- File types
- Upload behavior

This provides visibility into how data leaves the environment.

---

## Threat Intelligence Enrichment

Threat intelligence was used to investigate:

- Destination IP addresses
- Historical infrastructure relationships
- Reputation data
- Associated files and domains

A major lesson from this project is that a clean reputation score does not automatically mean an indicator is safe.

---

## Endpoint Detection and Response (EDR)

Endpoint analysis was performed to investigate:

- Process execution
- Discovery activity
- PowerShell activity
- Command-line arguments
- File staging behavior
- Remote access activity

The endpoint investigation helped determine what activity occurred on the host before the outbound transfer.

